The '''''Encyclopedia of the Roman Empire''''', written by [[Matthew Bunson]] in 1994 and published by [[Facts on File]], is a detailed depiction of the history of the [[Roman Empire]]. This work, of roughly 494 pages (a 2002 revised version containing 636 pages) stores more than 2,000 entries.

==Versions==
* US Hardcover revised edition (July 2002), published by Facts on File: {{ISBN|0-8160-4562-3}}

The book gives the reader much information about the life and decay of Rome, bringing the reader through an interesting voyage in time.

==References==

* Bunson, Matthew. ''Encyclopedia of the Roman Empire''. New York: Facts on File, 2013.

